{
  "stem": "8784.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And Adam Mandel was taken away with the group of 700 and eventually wound up in Mauthausen, and I stayed on at the factory of Oskar Schindler.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Following this reduction of the workforce from 1,000 to 300, not long after that a-- a spy plane, a English spy plane or Australian spy plane, flying over Krakow was either shot down or crashed over the city of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And of all the places, he crashes into our small camp of-- adjoining the factory of the enamel works of Oskar Schindler.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I remember that distinctly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were extremely fortunate, because he crashed into a barrack that was just vacated by those 700 people that were taken up to Krakow-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He crashed into a vacant barrack, into-- and in fact, did not hurt anyone in the group of 300 at all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The plane was full of ammunition.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I remember the ammunition popping all night, a fire burning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "In the morning, we-- after the fire subsided, we were able to get a little closer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And all I would see is the mountains of-- a mountain of these cartridges from the popped ammunition and a torso of a man still strapped in a seat of this plane.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "This was an English flyer or an Australian flyer that was burned in that crash.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We remained in this concentration camp for a while longer, until we-- until we-- and Schindler's duties by now were to actually pack and-- and be prepared to close up this factory on short notice because the Russians were advancing.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And evidently, he had his orders from Amon Goeth from the Krakow-Plaszow concentration camp, under whose supervision evidently he came, that he would have to liquidate.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So he was closing up some of the factory buildings.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
